The Open starts on Thursday, and sees Poulter tee off at 9.37am with Westwood at 2.38pm.

The latter, though, may be under added pressure after Europe's Ryder Cup captain Paul McGinley urged the 41-year-old to up his game in Liverpool.

'We all know Lee has the pedigree,' said McGinley.

'If you look back at the Ryder Cup since 1997, he has been the one constant pillar of all our success during that time.

'I'm a huge fan, and I'm certainly not looking to rip up the template. But I have to justify every decision I make, so he has to show me some form.'

